=============================================================
                 DEVOPS PREREQUISITES NOTES
=============================================================

DATA FORMATS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
XML
- Tag-based hierarchical format
- Used in Maven, Jenkins, SOAP APIs
- One root element required
- Attributes: <server enabled="true">
- Comments: <!-- comment -->
- Example:
  <server>
    <host>example.com</host>
    <port>8080</port>
    <enabled>true</enabled>
  </server>

JSON
- Key-value pairs (objects, arrays)
- Used in APIs, Terraform, AWS CLI outputs
- No comments allowed
- Example:
  {
    "server": {
      "host": "example.com",
      "port": 8080,
      "enabled": true
    }
  }
- CLI Tool: jq â†’ cat config.json | jq '.server.host'

YAML
- Indentation-based (spaces only)
- Used in Kubernetes, Ansible, Docker Compose, GitHub Actions
- Multi-line: | (literal), > (folded)
- Example:
  server:
    host: example.com
    port: 8080
    enabled: true

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
MYSQL
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation:
  wget https://dev.mysql.com/get/mysql-apt-config_0.8.36-1_all.deb
  sudo dpkg -i mysql-apt-config_0.8.36-1_all.deb
  sudo systemctl start mysql
  sudo systemctl status mysql

Connect & User Management:
  mysql -u root -p
  ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'New_Password';
  CREATE DATABASE db_name;
  USE db_name;
  CREATE USER 'john'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'New_Password';
  CREATE USER 'john'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'New_Password';
  GRANT SELECT, UPDATE ON db_name.* TO 'john'@'%';
  FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROGRAMMING LANGUAGES
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Node.js
- Install: sudo apt install nodejs npm
- Commands:
  npm init -y
  npm install express
  sudo npm install -g nodemon
- Check: node -v, npm -v

Python
- Install: sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv
- Virtual env:
  python3 -m venv venv
  source venv/bin/activate
  deactivate
- Pip usage:
  pip install requests
  pip uninstall requests
  pip freeze > requirements.txt
  pip install -r requirements.txt

Go
- Install: sudo apt install golang
- Manual latest: wget https://go.dev/dl/go1.22.2.linux-amd64.tar.gz
  sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.22.2.linux-amd64.tar.gz
  export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin
  go version
- Go modules:
  mkdir myapp && cd myapp
  go mod init myapp
  go get github.com/gin-gonic/gin
  go run main.go

Ruby
- Install: sudo apt install ruby-full
- Commands: gem install rails, gem list, gem uninstall rails

Java
- Install: sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk maven
- Commands: java -version, mvn -v, mvn clean install, mvn package

C / C++
- Install: sudo apt install build-essential
- Check: gcc --version, g++ --version

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SYSTEM PACKAGE MANAGEMENT
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Debian/Ubuntu:
- Search: apt search <pkg>
- Install .deb: sudo dpkg -i file.deb
- Upgrade: sudo apt upgrade
- Remove: sudo apt remove <pkg>
- Fix broken: sudo apt --fix-broken install
- Reinstall: sudo apt install --reinstall <pkg>
- Clean cache: sudo apt clean && sudo apt autoclean
- List installed: apt list --installed

RHEL/Fedora:
- Search: dnf search <pkg>
- Install .rpm: sudo rpm -ivh file.rpm
- Upgrade: sudo dnf upgrade
- Remove: sudo dnf remove <pkg>
- Reinstall: sudo dnf reinstall <pkg>
- Clean cache: sudo dnf clean all

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PRODUCTION & DEPLOYMENT
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Python Production:
- Gunicorn, uWSGI, Gevent, Twisted Web
- Example: gunicorn main.app
- With workers: gunicorn main.app -w 2

Node.js Production:
- Use PM2 or systemd for process management

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FULL SETUP EXAMPLE (Ubuntu)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip nodejs npm golang ruby-full \
openjdk-17-jdk maven git docker.io

Check versions:
  python3 --version
  pip3 --version
  node -v
  npm -v
  go version
  ruby -v
  java -version

